  "prompt": "How do I get IR with my Samsung Galaxy 7 so I can use my phone as a TV remote?",
  "response": "The Samsung Galaxy S7 does not have a built-in infrared (IR) blaster like some earlier Samsung models. Therefore, you cannot use it directly as a universal TV remote.\n\nHowever, you have a few alternative options:\n\n1. Samsung Smart View App\n- Use the Samsung Smart View app to control compatible Samsung Smart TVs over WiFi\n- Works only with newer Samsung smart TVs\n\n2. Third-Party Remote Control Apps\n- Some apps like SURE Universal Remote can use your phone's Wi-Fi or cellular connection to control certain smart TVs\n- May require specific TV compatibility\n\n3. External IR Blaster Accessories\n- Some external IR blaster dongles can plug into your phone's charging port\n- These add IR remote functionality to phones that don't have a built-in blaster\n\n4. Smart Home Hubs\n- Devices like Harmony Hub can help you control multiple devices via smartphone app\n- Often work with a wide range of TV and entertainment system brands\n\nUnfortunately, the Galaxy S7 does not have a native IR blaster built into the phone itself, so you'll need to use one of these alternative methods.",
